articles.author: Dr. Jennifer Miao
articles.title: Eating a dozen eggs a week doesn't hurt your cholesterol: Study - Good Morning America
articles.description: A new study found no meaningful change in levels of "good" and "bad" cholesterol in people who ate a dozen eggs a week.
articles.content: Eating more than a dozen fortified eggs each week did not negatively affect cholesterol levels compared to an egg-free diet among U.S. adults aged 50 or older, according to a new study to be presente… [+2777 chars]
